"Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]}]},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":2,"title":"Caffeine Control Rule","instructions":["Follow this rule strictly:","No caffeine after 2 PM","coffee","tea","energy drinks","pre-workout drinks","Caffeine can stay in the body 6–8 hours, delaying sleep onset."],"whyThisWorks":"Small consistent actions reinforce stability and support restful sleep."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Evening Nervous System Downshift","steps":["About 60 minutes before bed, listen to your guided sleep meditation audio.","Lie comfortably in bed.","Play the meditation audio at low volume.","Close your eyes and follow the instructions.","Allow your body to relax naturally.","Recommended length: 10–20 minutes."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"audio","title":"Tonight''s Guided Sleep Audio","description":"Press play during your evening wind-down or once you are in bed.","audioStoragePath":"sleep_disorder_reset/day-06.mp3","durationSeconds":642},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Body Temperature Sleep Trick","steps":["Take a warm shower 60–90 minutes before sleep.","After the shower, your body temperature naturally drops, which signals the brain to prepare for","sleep."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The Military Sleep Method (fast Sleep Technique)","steps":["Once in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying in a quiet mountain valley at night.","The air is cool and peaceful.","Everything around you is still and calm.","Focus on the scene while breathing slowly."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The “Brain Dump” Method","steps":["Many people cannot sleep because the brain keeps thinking about tasks, worries, or tomorrow’s","problems.","About 30 minutes before bed, take a notebook and write down:","everything on your mind","tasks for tomorrow","worries or thoughts","Do not organize it. Just empty your mind onto paper."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 6?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 6 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"quieter thoughts at night"}]'::jsonb
