ions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Pushups","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"12 Reps × 4 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Jumping Jacks","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"25 Reps × 3 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Standing Forward Stretch","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"10 Slow Repetitions","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]}]},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":2,"title":"Caffeine Control Rule","instructions":["Follow this rule strictly:","No caffeine after 2 PM","coffee","tea","energy drinks","pre-workout drinks","Caffeine can remain in the body 6–8 hours, disturbing sleep cycles."],"whyThisWorks":"Small consistent actions reinforce stability and support restful sleep."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Evening Nervous System Downshift","steps":["About 60 minutes before bed, listen to your guided sleep meditation audio.","Lie comfortably in bed.","Play the meditation audio at low volume.","Close your eyes and follow the instructions.","Allow the body to relax naturally.","Recommended length: 10–20 minutes."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"audio","title":"Tonight''s Guided Sleep Audio","description":"Press play during your evening wind-down or once you are in bed.","audioStoragePath":"sleep_disorder_reset/day-10.mp3","durationSeconds":652},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Body Temperature Sleep Trick","steps":["Take a warm shower 60–90 minutes before sleep.","After the shower, your body temperature drops slightly, which signals the brain that it is time to","sleep."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The Military Sleep Method (fast Sleep Technique)","steps":["Once in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying beside a quiet river under a starry sky.","You hear gentle water flowing and the night is peaceful.","Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The “Mental Countdown”","steps":["This trick helps interrupt racing thoughts.","While lying in bed, slowly count backwards from 100."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 10?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 10 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"stronger sleepiness at night"}]'::jsonb
