th steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Pushups","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"20 Reps × 5 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Jumping Jacks","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"50 Reps × 4 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Plank Hold","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"40 Seconds × 4 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Standing Forward Stretch","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]}]},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":2,"title":"Caffeine Control Rule","instructions":["Follow this rule strictly:","No caffeine after 2 PM","coffee","tea","energy drinks","pre-workout drinks","Caffeine can stay active in the body 6–8 hours, disturbing sleep cycles."],"whyThisWorks":"Small consistent actions reinforce stability and support restful sleep."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Evening Nervous System Downshift","steps":["About 60 minutes before bed, listen to your guided sleep meditation audio.","Lie comfortably in bed.","Play the meditation audio at low volume.","Close your eyes and follow the instructions.","Allow your body to relax naturally.","Recommended length: 10–20 minutes."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"audio","title":"Tonight''s Guided Sleep Audio","description":"Press play during your evening wind-down or once you are in bed.","audioStoragePath":"sleep_disorder_reset/day-16.mp3","durationSeconds":576},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Body Temperature Sleep Trick","steps":["Take a warm shower 60–90 minutes before sleep.","After the shower, the body temperature naturally drops, signaling the brain that it is time to sleep."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The Military Sleep Method (fast Sleep Technique)","steps":["Once in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying beside a quiet river under a peaceful night sky.","The sound of water is gentle and relaxing.","Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The “Cognitive Defusion Trick”","steps":["Sometimes thoughts keep repeating in the mind at night.","Instead of fighting the thought, label it and let it pass.","When a thought appears, say silently:","“This is just a thought.”","Then let it pass and return to slow breathing.","Do not analyze or continue the thought."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 16?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 16 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"fewer racing thoughts"}]'::jsonb
