tice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The Military Sleep Method (fast Sleep Technique)","steps":["Once in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying in a quiet forest clearing under the moonlight.","The air is cool and peaceful.","Everything around you is calm and silent.","Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The “Foot Massage Relaxation”","steps":["The feet contain many nerve endings connected to the nervous system.","Relaxing them before bed can help the entire body relax.","Before sleeping:","Sit comfortably on the bed.","Gently massage the bottom of each foot.","Apply light pressure using your thumbs.","Massage for 2–3 minutes per foot."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 17?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 17 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"deeper sleep"}]'::jsonb
